hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: What line of work are you in? thepharmacyone-24.com Such judgments are entirely subjective, of course, so I call Montgomery to ask for his opinion as a traditional farmer from Kent, the so-called Garden of England. I had expected some ambivalence at least, but he offers a surprisingly robust endorsement of Thanet Earth. He would not have sold his land had he not believed in the project, he says. 'The image of a farmer with his horse and cart is pretty much past. Technology is pushing us all forward. I think it’s a very positive development... I see absolutely no reason why what’s coming out of there is not as good, flavour-wise, as what you can get anywhere else.’
